The paper deals with reasoning about exceptions in ontologies, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence and knowledge representation. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of description logics, which is a subfield of logic and theoretical computer science, making cs.LO another likely sub-category. The paper also touches on the topic of defeasible reasoning, which is related to the sub-category of cs.CR (computational complexity). Additionally, the paper discusses the construction of a base for the skeptical closure, which is related to the sub-categories of cs.DB (databases) and cs.SE (software engineering).
